OL,7,F"Wales was also too small to escape
OL,8,Fbeing parochial and limited in what it
OL,9,Fcould do locally to really change its
OL,10,Foutcomes."
OL,12,FMr Friedman also criticised two
OL,13,Fleading advisers to the Welsh
OL,14,FGovernment, Chief Medical Officer Dr
OL,15,FFrank Atherton and Chief Scientific
OL,16,FAdviser Dr Rob Orford.
